Plea Negotiations
Plea negotiation practices are another crucial element in prison population forecasts, because more than 85% of all federal defendants enter guilty pleas. We made two assumptions: (1) that, as we projected the 1985 cohort forward in time, the same defendants who entered guilty pleas in the past would enter guilty pleas in the future; and (2) that the percentage reduction received currently for a guilty plea (30 to 40% reduction in time served) would prevail in the future.

